                            <AssayComments>The epitope recognized by Fab RU5 bound to the vWF A3 domain was determined by X-ray crystallography. There are three molecules in the crystallographic asymmetric unit. PDB chains for each complex are: Complex A : Antibody heavy-chain: H, Antibody light-chain: L, epitope chain: A. Complex B : Antibody heavy-chain: I, Antibody light-chain: M, epitope chain: B. Complex C : Antibody heavy-chain: J, Antibody light-chain: N, epitope chain: C. In the three complexes, the RU5/A3 interaction region is well conserved, but relatively large differences are shown in the orientations of the RU5 constant domains with respect to its variable domains and A3. Complexes B and C form a tightly interacting anti-parallel dimer and are related by 2-fold non-crystallographic symmetry. Complex A forms a similar anti-parallel dimer with a crystallographically related complex A'.</AssayComments>
                        </AssayInformation>
