                            <Comments>Antibody CDR loops L1 and L2 interact with loops α1β2 and α3β4. All six CDR loops interact with A3 residues in the contiguous segment formed by loop β3α2 and helix α2. Conformational comparison between RU5 Fab/A3 (this structure), unbound A3 [PDB: 1AO3] and unbound A3 [PDB: 1ATZ]  showed that overall, the structure of the A3 molecule is the same as the structures of the unbound A3. There are three conformational diverse loops located in the antibody epitope α1β2, β3α2 and α3β4. Specifically loop α1β2 has a unique conformation in the RU5 Fab/A3 complex, indicating that this conformation is induced by RU5. Also, distant from the RU5 epitope conformational variation is observed for loops β1α1 and α5β6.</Comments>
